extends java.lang.Object

SatelliteLocation

public SatelliteLocation(java.lang.String name,
                         java.util.Date beginTime,
                         java.util.Date endTime,
                         CoordinateSystem coordSystem,
                         TupleXYZ[] coordinates)
Constructs a SatelliteLocation object with the give attributes.

Parameters:
name - is the name of the satellite
beginTime - is the begining time of the location information
endTime - is the ending time of the location information
coordSystem - specifies the coordinate system in which the location information is provided
coordinates - contains location of the satellite as cartesian coordinates over the even distribution of time between beginTime and endTime

getCoordinateSystem

public java.lang.String getCoordinateSystem()
Provides the coordinate system in which the location information is provided.

Returns:
the String representation of the CoordinateSystem value. The String representation is returned to comply with JAX-RPC 1.0 EA2 data type restrictions. It should be converted back to a CoordinateSystem object whenever possible to ensure type safety.
See Also:
CoordinateSystem#getInstance, setCoordinateSystem(String)

setCoordinates

public void setCoordinates(TupleXYZ[] coordinates)
Sets the coordinates of the satellite between times beginTime and endTime.

Parameters:
coordinates - are the satellite's coordinates. Coordinate[0][0] is the X coordinate at beginTime. Coordinate[0][1] is the Y coordinate at beginTime. Coordinate[0][2] is the Z coordinate at beginTime. Coordinate[length - 1][0] is the X coordinate at endTime.
See Also:
getCoordinates()

getCoordinates

public TupleXYZ[] getCoordinates()
Provides the coordinates of the satellite between times beginTime and endTime. Coordinate[0][0] is the X coordinate at beginTime. Coordinate[0][1] is the Y coordinate at beginTime. Coordinate[0][2] is the Z coordinate at beginTime. Coordinate[length - 1][0] is the X coordinate at endTime.

Returns:
the satellite's coordinates
